Abandoned pits turn into death traps             Stephen Rutto and Fred Kibor   23rd Sep 2019 00:00:00 GMT +0300 Stephen Rutto and Fred Kibor   23rd Sep 2019 00:00:00 GMT +0300 Stephen Rutto and Fred Kibor   Residents mill around a borrow pit abandoned by a road contractor in Kipkabus, Uasin Gishu County on Sunday, September 15, 2019. At least seven people have drowned and died in borrow pits this year alone in the North Rift. [Stephen Rutto, Standard]  Residents mill around a borrow pit abandoned by a road contractor in Kipkabus, Uasin Gishu County on Sunday, September 15, 2019. At least seven people have drowned and died in borrow pits this year alone in the North Rift. [Stephen Rutto, Standard] Residents mill around a borrow pit abandoned by a road contractor in Kipkabus, Uasin Gishu County on Sunday, September 15, 2019. At least seven people have drowned and died in borrow pits this year alone in the North Rift. [Stephen Rutto, Standard] Residents mill around a borrow pit abandoned by a road contractor in Kipkabus, Uasin Gishu County on Sunday, September 15, 2019. At least seven people have drowned and died in borrow pits this year alone in the North Rift.         For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper. For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.                     We are undertaking a survey to help us improve our content for you. This will only take 1 minute of your time, please give us your feedback by clicking HERE. All responses will be confidential. We are undertaking a survey to help us improve our content for you. This will only take 1 minute of your time, please give us your feedback by clicking HERE. All responses will be confidential. HERE Related Topics Evans Kimutai Chinese contractor Nayaru-Iten road Death traps